---
import BaseLayout from '../components/BaseLayout.astro';
import OriginMark from '../components/OriginMark.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Founding Document: The Final Inch — OurOrigin"
  description="OurOrigin exists because the people and places behind real products deserve to be seen, not kept in the background of a marketing story."
  canonicalPath="/why"
  ogTitle="The Founding Document: The Final Inch | OurOrigin"
  ogDescription="A small business sourcing from the Western Ghats. We show you the origin and let you reach your own conclusions."
  navVariant="light"
  showFooter={true}
>
    <main id="main-content" class="dossier-container">
        <div class="guide-line"></div>

        <div class="gsap-reveal">
            <h1 class="document-title">The Final Inch</h1>
            <p class="preamble">You are standing at the final inch of a very long journey. You are no longer just a spectator; you are inside the origin.</p>
        </div>

        <section class="dossier-section gsap-reveal">
            <div class="decorator-mark">
                <OriginMark variant="gold" size={24} animate={false} />
            </div>
            <h2 class="section-header">01 — The Legacy</h2>
            <p class="prose-block">Before there was a brand, before there was a product, there was a profound legacy of dignity and ecological intelligence.</p>
            <p class="prose-block">Consider a farmer who walks 12 kilometres into a forest. He picks what is ripe. He leaves what the animals took, because it was theirs. He leaves what the season hasn't finished. He carries back only what the forest agreed to give.</p>
            <p class="prose-block">This is just one story among many. Across all origins, there exists a deep mastery of the environment. These are not people waiting to be saved or uplifted; they possess a legacy and dignity that conventional systems fail to recognize.</p>
            <p class="prose-block">OurOrigin exists because we believe this legacy is the most vital part of the journey. Making it visible is an act of deep respect.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="dossier-section gsap-reveal">
            <div class="decorator-mark">
                <OriginMark variant="primary" size={24} animate={false} />
            </div>
            <h2 class="section-header">02 — What an Origin Actually Is</h2>
            <p class="prose-block">An origin is not a location. A location is a coordinate on a map, and a map is an abstraction.</p>
            <p class="prose-block">An origin is the living reality beneath the surface. It is the place — its altitude, its rainfall, its soil, its particular quality of morning light. It is the knowledge — accumulated across generations, in the same forest, watching the same vines, understanding what ready looks like before it is visible to someone who has not been watching long enough.</p>
            <p class="prose-block">The pepper that arrives in a kitchen is the final visible inch of all of this. The packet it comes in is not the product. It is the evidence.</p>
            <p class="prose-block">When we say "origin," we mean all of it. Not the romantic version. Not the marketing version. The actual version, in all its complexity and specificity and non-repeatability.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="dossier-section gsap-reveal">
            <div class="decorator-mark">
                <OriginMark variant="gold" size={24} animate={false} />
            </div>
            <h2 class="section-header">03 — The Seven Dimensions</h2>
            <p class="prose-block">An origin can be understood through seven dimensions. None is more important than the others. None exists independently.</p>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
                <li><strong>Geo</strong> — the specific place. Not "India" or "the Western Ghats" as a brand claim, but Wayanad at 900-1,100 metres, Idukki on its steep slopes at 1,200 metres, Nilgiris high enough for frost.</li>
                <li><strong>Bio</strong> — the life the place produces. The ecology, the species, the relationships between what grows and what doesn't.</li>
                <li><strong>Community</strong> — the people who understand and live within this ecosystem. Not beneficiaries of a development programme. Knowledge holders. Practitioners.</li>
                <li><strong>Method</strong> — the relationship between community and nature, expressed through practice. How the vine is climbed. How readiness is recognised.</li>
                <li><strong>Product</strong> — the yield. The final visible form that the other dimensions produce together. The product is the evidence that the others are real.</li>
                <li><strong>Observation</strong> — the evidence layer. The documented record of what actually happens: what was harvested, when, at what conditions, by whom.</li>
                <li><strong>Time</strong> — the living layer. Origins change by season. The live weather at Wayanad's coordinates is not decoration. It is evidence that this is a place experiencing real conditions right now.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="dossier-section gsap-reveal">
            <div class="decorator-mark">
                <OriginMark variant="primary" size={24} animate={false} />
            </div>
            <h2 class="section-header">04 — Inside the Origin</h2>
            <p class="prose-block">This is the most important structural claim OurOrigin makes, and it is not a marketing claim. It is a description of how the system actually works.</p>
            <p class="prose-block">The farmer who walked 12 kilometres made a decision: to pick only what was ready, to leave what wasn't. That decision has no value without a market that understands and pays for it. A market that pays the same price for carelessly harvested pepper as for carefully harvested pepper is a market that makes the farmer's decision economically irrational. Over time, it eliminates the decision. The knowledge goes too.</p>
            <p class="prose-block">The buyer who understands what they're paying for — who pays for the 12km walk, the leaving, the not-harvesting-for-maximum-yield — makes the corresponding decision: to pay what this actually costs, and to know why it costs that. This decision completes the farmer's decision.</p>
            <p class="prose-block">The origin is a closed system only when both decisions hold. The consumer is not downstream from the origin. They are inside it.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="dossier-section gsap-reveal">
            <div class="decorator-mark">
                <OriginMark variant="gold" size={24} animate={false} />
            </div>
            <h2 class="section-header">05 — What We Will Always Do</h2>
            <p class="prose-block"><strong>01. The Origin Remains the Protagonist.</strong> The product is merely the physical evidence that the origin exists. We will never strip a product of its context to make it easier to consume.</p>
            <p class="prose-block"><strong>02. No Exploitation of Vulnerability.</strong> We will not create pseudo-vulnerability or use charity as a marketing tool. We respect the inherent dignity and legacy of every community we work with.</p>
            <p class="prose-block"><strong>03. Connection Over Commerce.</strong> We are creating a connection. The market is just the final one inch of this journey. The packaging, the physical item, is a bridge to the origin, not the end of the story.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="dossier-section gsap-reveal">
            <div class="decorator-mark">
                <OriginMark variant="primary" size={24} animate={false} />
            </div>
            <h2 class="section-header">06 — The Standard</h2>
            <p class="prose-block">When you ask "Why this?", the answer must always point back to the source.</p>
            <p class="prose-block">If any decision—any partnership, any communication, any element of this experience—does not reflect the dignity of the 12-kilometre walk, or the profound legacy of the communities we work with, it is the wrong decision.</p>
        </section>

        <div class="conclusion gsap-reveal">
            <OriginMark variant="gold" size={64} animate={false} />
            <div class="conclusion-sig">You Are Inside the Origin</div>
        </div>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
    /* Dossier Layout */
    .dossier-container {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 25vh 5vw 15vh 5vw;
        position: relative;
    }

    /* Telemetry Guide Line */
    .guide-line {
        position: absolute;
        left: 5vw;
        top: 0;
        bottom: 0;
        width: 1px;
        background: linear-gradient(to bottom, transparent, rgba(244, 241, 235, 0.1) 10%, rgba(244, 241, 235, 0.1) 90%, transparent);
        z-index: 0;
    }

    @media (min-width: 900px) {
        .guide-line {
            left: calc(50% - 480px);
        }
    }

    /* Typographic System */
    .document-title {
        font-family: var(--font-mono);
        font-size: 0.75rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.3em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--color-gold);
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
        opacity: 0.8;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 1rem;
    }

    .document-title::after {
        content: '';
        flex-grow: 1;
        height: 1px;
        background-color: rgba(166, 124, 60, 0.3);
        max-width: 200px;
    }

    .preamble {
        font-family: var(--font-display);
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        line-height: 1.4;
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--color-warm-cream);
        opacity: 0.7;
        margin-bottom: 8rem;
        max-width: 700px;
    }

    /* Sections */
    .dossier-section {
        margin-bottom: 8rem;
        position: relative;
        padding-left: 2rem;
    }

    .section-header {
        font-family: var(--font-mono);
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.2em;
        color: var(--color-gold);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .prose-block {
        font-family: var(--font-display);
        font-size: 1.4rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: var(--color-warm-cream);
        max-width: 680px;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .prose-block strong {
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--color-gold);
    }

    .bullet-list {
        list-style: none;
        padding-left: 0;
        margin-top: 2rem;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .bullet-list li {
        font-family: var(--font-display);
        font-size: 1.4rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: var(--color-warm-cream);
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        position: relative;
        padding-left: 1.5rem;
        max-width: 680px;
    }

    .bullet-list li::before {
        content: '—';
        position: absolute;
        left: 0;
        color: var(--color-gold);
        opacity: 0.5;
    }

    /* Visual Decorators */
    .decorator-mark {
        position: absolute;
        left: -1rem;
        top: 0.2rem;
        opacity: 0.3;
        transform: translateX(-50%);
    }

    .conclusion {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 15vh;
        padding-top: 5vh;
        border-top: 1px solid rgba(244, 241, 235, 0.1);
    }

    .conclusion-sig {
        font-family: var(--font-mono);
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.25em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--color-gold);
        margin-top: 3rem;
        opacity: 0.6;
    }

    /* GSAP fallback */
    @media (scripting: none) {
        .gsap-reveal {
            opacity: 1 !important;
            transform: none !important;
        }
    }
</style>

<script>
    import gsap from 'gsap';
    import { ScrollTrigger } from 'gsap/ScrollTrigger';

    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
        gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger);

        const reveals = document.querySelectorAll('.gsap-reveal');
        gsap.set(reveals, { opacity: 0, y: 30 });

        reveals.forEach((element) => {
            gsap.to(element, {
                scrollTrigger: {
                    trigger: element,
                    start: "top 85%",
                    toggleActions: "play none none reverse"
                },
                opacity: 1,
                y: 0,
                duration: 1.2,
                ease: "power2.out"
            });
        });
    });
</script>
